history.content:
-- COMPENSATED STUDY OPPORTUNITY FOR COMPUTER SCIENCE STUDENTS (BEGINNERS WANTED!) --
Hello, CS students! Are you interested in trying an experimental programming tutorial? I’m a student researcher in UC Berkeley EECS. We’re conducting a study on improving CS education--specifically to find out if exciting new programming tools can help students learn CS. It is totally okay if you've only taken an intro to programming class!
Study sessions are MAX 90 minutes, and participants will receive a $30 Amazon gift card. If you think you might be interested, please sign up at https://tinyurl.com/introcsstudy! (Don’t worry, filling out the Google form isn’t a commitment to participate!) And if you have any questions, feel free to email me at dhanyajayagopal@berkeley.edu.
history.subject: Compensated Study for CS Beginners!
